title: Spain Elections: Results Show No Party With Enough Votes to Govern
description: The returns showed no party winning the support needed to govern, leaving the country facing weeks of uncertainty.

title: Your Monday Briefing: A Major Vote in Israel
description: Also, Cambodia’s elections, Ukraine’s counteroffensive and Japan’s coal plants.

title: Israel’s Identity Hangs in the Balance Over Judicial Overhaul
description: Lawmakers are set to vote Monday on whether to limit the Supreme Court’s power as one element of a government plan to overhaul judicial authority. It is part of a profound rift over Israel’s nature and future.

title: Wildfires on Rhodes, Greece, Force Thousands to Evacuate
description: As firefighters fought blazes kindled by tinder-dry conditions on the Greek island, the authorities sent tourists and residents to schools, gyms and boats moored at the port for shelter.

title: Weary Soldiers, Unreliable Munitions: Ukraine’s Many Challenges
description: A month of reporting by New York Times journalists found the fighting mostly stalemated and Ukraine facing an array of obstacles against a determined foe.

title: Israel Protests: Protests Swell On Eve of Key Judicial Vote That Has Split Israel
description: Lawmakers are debating the right-wing government’s judicial overhaul, which has sparked months of demonstrations. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, who backs the plan, underwent a heart procedure on Sunday.

title: Russian Missiles Strike Cathedral, Apartments in Odesa
description: Russia has renewed its attacks on the port city after it pulled out of the Black Sea grain deal last week.

title: In Iran, It’s Scorching Hot and Water Supplies Are Shrinking
description: Water shortages from longtime mismanagement have left people with shrinking options, as temperatures spike and growing poverty makes air-conditioning unaffordable for many.

title: 1 Dead in Odesa as Russia Strikes Cathedral and Apartment Buildings
description: Russia has renewed its attacks on the port city after it pulled out of the Black Sea grain deal last week.

title: Netanyahu Hospitalized for Heart Defect as Israel’s Turmoil Intensifies
description: Doctors said Benjamin Netanyahu, the Israeli prime minister, was “doing very well” after an unexpected heart operation early Sunday. But the news compounded the chaos prompted by a government plan to limit judicial power.

title: What to Know About Spain’s Election on Sunday
description: The national elections could see a far-right party enter the Spanish government for the first time since the 1970s.
